        <li><strong>Production-Ready Specs</strong>: Support various aspect ratios and resolutions from 512px to 4K, ensuring visuals stay sharp for vertical social posts or wide-screen backdrops.</li>
        <li><strong>Visual Fidelity Upgrade</strong>: Delivers vibrant lighting, richer textures, and sharper details, maintaining high-quality aesthetics at Flash speed.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h2>Multi-Platform Rollout</h2>
      <p>Nano Banana 2 is rolling out today across Google products:</p>
      
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Gemini App</strong>: Replaces Nano Banana Pro across Fast, Thinking, and Pro models. Pro and Ultra subscribers retain access to Pro version via three-dot menu regeneration.</li>
        <li><strong>Google Search</strong>: Available in AI Mode and Lens, supporting 141 new countries/territories and eight additional languages.</li>
        <li><strong>AI Studio + API</strong>: Available in preview in AI Studio and Gemini API.</li>
        <li><strong>Google Cloud</strong>: Available in preview with Gemini API in Vertex AI.</li>
        <li><strong>Flow</strong>: New default image generation model, available to all Flow users at zero credits.</li>
        <li><strong>Google Ads</strong>: Powers suggestions while creating campaigns.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h2>Content Provenance and Verification</h2>
      <p>Google continues deepening its provenance approach by coupling SynthID technology with C2PA Content Credentials to help identify and verify AI-generated content.</p>
      
      <p>Read the full article at <a href="https://blog.google/innovation-and-ai/technology/ai/nano-banana-2/">https://blog.google/innovation-and-ai/technology/ai/nano-banana-2/</a></p>
